This article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama in 2011, declaring June 19th as Father's Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of fathers in shaping the lives of their children and supporting fatherhood in families and communities. It acknowledges the absence of fathers and the impact it has on children, families, and communities. The article highlights the initiatives and efforts of the Obama administration in supporting fathers and their communities, such as the Fatherhood and Mentoring Initiative and promoting work-life balance. The proclamation calls upon all citizens to observe Father's Day with appropriate programs and activities.